We write two functions: one function to download files and another to unzipping¶

In [3]:
def download(url,name):
    data=open(path_input+name,"wb") 
    content = requests.get(url) 
    data.write(content.content) 
    data.close()
    
def uncompress(name):
    tar = tarfile.open(path_input+name, "r:gz")
    tar.extractall()
    tar.close()
    os.remove(path_input+name)

print("Downloading zip with image dataset...")    
download('https://www.robots.ox.ac.uk/~vgg/data/flowers/102/102flowers.tgz','102_dataset')  
print("Unzipping...")
uncompress('102_dataset')
print("Delete zip file...")
print("Downloading image labels...") 
download('https://www.robots.ox.ac.uk/~vgg/data/flowers/102/imagelabels.mat','labels')

Now we create function that create folders for each dataset and each class and sort files¶

In [11]:
def field_sort(array):
    s=0
    for i in array:
        if s==0:
            folder='/train'
        elif s==1:
            folder='/test'   
        elif s==2:
            folder='/validation' 
        s+=1    
        try:
            os.mkdir(path_input+folder)
        except OSError:
            pass  
        classes= i['label'].unique()
        for clas in classes:
            try:
                os.mkdir(path_input+folder+"/"+str(clas))
            except OSError:
                pass  
            files=i[i['label']==clas]['img'].tolist()   
            for file in files:
                shutil.move(file, path_input+folder+'/'+str(clas)+'/')
    os.rmdir(path_input+'jpg')
field_sort([train,test,validation])

Now we create generators to transform our train data and only rescale validation data¶

In [12]:
BATCH_SIZE = 64
image_width, image_height = 224,224
train_dir=path_input+'train/'
validation_dir=path_input+'validation/'
test_dir=path_input+'test/'

image_gen_train = ImageDataGenerator(
    rescale=1./255,
    rotation_range=40,
    width_shift_range=0.2,
    height_shift_range=0.2,
    shear_range=0.2,
    zoom_range=0.2,
    horizontal_flip=True,
    fill_mode='nearest'
)

image_gen_val = ImageDataGenerator(rescale=1./255)

image_gen_test = ImageDataGenerator( rescale = 1./255. )

train_data_gen = image_gen_train.flow_from_directory(batch_size=BATCH_SIZE,
                                                     directory=train_dir,
                                                     shuffle=True,
                                                     target_size=(image_width, image_height),
                                                     class_mode='categorical')

val_data_gen = image_gen_val.flow_from_directory(batch_size=BATCH_SIZE,
                                                 directory=validation_dir,
                                                 target_size=(image_width, image_height),
                                                 class_mode='categorical')

test_data_gen =  image_gen_test.flow_from_directory(
                    test_dir,
                    batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, 
                    class_mode='categorical',
                    shuffle=False,
                    target_size=(image_width, image_height))

Demonstrate the generators work¶

In [13]:
def plotImages(images_arr):
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 5, figsize=(20,20))
    axes = axes.flatten()
    for img, ax in zip(images_arr, axes):
        ax.imshow(img)
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

augmented_images = [train_data_gen[0][0][0] for i in range(5)]
plotImages(augmented_images)

Now we can train our model with pre-trained models with transfer learning¶

We use two models:
-VGG16
-Xception

1 - VGG16¶

In [15]:
modelCheckpoint = ModelCheckpoint(path_input+'best_model_vgg.hdf5', save_best_only = True)
monitor_val_acc = EarlyStopping(monitor='val_accuracy', 
                       patience=15)

image_input = Input(shape=(224, 224, 3))
model = VGG16(input_tensor=image_input, include_top=True,weights='imagenet')
# model.summary()
last_layer = model.get_layer('block5_pool').output
x= Flatten(name='flatten')(last_layer)
x = Dense(4096, activation='relu', name='fc1')(x)
x = keras.layers.Dropout(0.1)(x)
x = Dense(4096, activation='relu', name='fc2')(x)
x = keras.layers.Dropout(0.1)(x)
out = Dense(102, activation='softmax', name='output')(x)
custom_vgg_model = Model(image_input, out)
for layer in custom_vgg_model.layers[:-3]:
    layer.trainable = False
    
custom_vgg_model.compile(loss='categorical_crossentropy',optimizer='adam',metrics=['accuracy'])
history_vgg = custom_vgg_model.fit_generator(
            train_data_gen,
            callbacks = [monitor_val_acc,modelCheckpoint],
            validation_data=val_data_gen,
            epochs=150
)
custom_vgg_model.load_weights('best_model_vgg.hdf5')

In [27]:
modelCheckpoint = ModelCheckpoint(path_input+'best_model_xception.hdf5', save_best_only = True)
monitor_val_acc = EarlyStopping(monitor='val_accuracy', 
                       patience=10)

image_input = Input(shape=(224, 224, 3))
model = Xception(input_tensor=image_input, include_top=True,weights='imagenet')
# model.summary()
last_layer = model.get_layer('block14_sepconv2_act').output
x= Flatten(name='flatten')(last_layer)
x = Dense(4096, activation='relu', name='fc1')(x)
x = keras.layers.Dropout(0.2)(x)
x = Dense(4096, activation='relu', name='fc2')(x)
x = keras.layers.Dropout(0.2)(x)
out = Dense(102, activation='softmax', name='output')(x)
custom_xception_model = Model(image_input, out)
for layer in custom_xception_model.layers[:-1]:
    layer.trainable = False
    
custom_xception_model.compile(loss='categorical_crossentropy',optimizer='adam',metrics=['accuracy'])
history_xception = custom_xception_model.fit_generator(
            train_data_gen,
            callbacks = [monitor_val_acc,modelCheckpoint],
            validation_data=val_data_gen,
            epochs=150
)

custom_xception_model.load_weights('best_model_xception.hdf5')
